 {"id":"jeffreysprompts.com-7l29","title":"Implement keyboard shortcuts reference modal","description":"## Origin
Mirror from jeffreysprompts_premium jeffreysprompts_premium-axfu. Keep both repos in sync.

## Task
Create a discoverable keyboard shortcuts reference modal.

## Why This Matters
- Helps users learn shortcuts
- Power user feature discovery
- Accessibility improvement
- Professional UX

## Features

### 1. Shortcuts Modal
- Press ? to open
- Categorized shortcuts
- Search shortcuts
- Visual key display

### 2. Shortcut Categories
| Category | Examples |
|----------|----------|
| Navigation | G+D (Dashboard), G+L (Library) |
| Actions | N (New prompt), S (Save) |
| Search | / (Focus search), Esc (Clear) |
| Editor | Cmd+B (Bold), Cmd+I (Italic) |
| Selection | Cmd+A (Select all), Shift+Click |

### 3. Key Display
- Platform-aware (Cmd vs Ctrl)
- Visual key caps
- Combination indicators (+)
- Sequence indicators (then)

### 4. Customization (Premium)
- Customize shortcuts
- Conflict detection
- Reset to defaults
- Import/export

## Implementation

### Shortcuts Registry
```typescript
const shortcuts: ShortcutConfig[] = [
  {
    id: 'new-prompt',
    keys: ['n'],
    description: 'Create new prompt',
    category: 'actions',
    action: () => router.push('/prompts/new'),
    when: 'not-editing',
  },
  {
    id: 'save',
    keys: ['mod+s'],
    description: 'Save current item',
    category: 'actions',
    action: () => save(),
    when: 'editing',
  },
  {
    id: 'search',
    keys: ['/'],
    description: 'Focus search',
    category: 'search',
    action: () => searchRef.current?.focus(),
    when: 'not-editing',
  },
];
```

### Shortcuts Provider
```typescript
function ShortcutsProvider({ children }) {
  useEffect(() => {
    const handler = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
      // Check for ? to open modal
      if (e.key === '?' && !isEditing()) {
        setShowModal(true);
        return;
      }

      // Find matching shortcut
      const shortcut = findMatchingShortcut(e, shortcuts);
      if (shortcut && canExecute(shortcut)) {
        e.preventDefault();
        shortcut.action();
      }
    };

    window.addEventListener('keydown', handler);
    return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handler);
  }, []);

  return (
    <ShortcutsContext.Provider value={{ shortcuts, showModal, setShowModal }}>
      {children}
      <ShortcutsModal />
    </ShortcutsContext.Provider>
  );
}
```

### Modal Component
```tsx
function ShortcutsModal() {
  const { shortcuts, showModal, setShowModal } = useShortcuts();
  const [search, setSearch] = useState('');

  const grouped = groupBy(shortcuts, 'category');
  const filtered = filterBySearch(grouped, search);

  return (
    <Dialog open={showModal} onOpenChange={setShowModal}>
      <DialogContent className="max-w-2xl">
        <DialogHeader>
          <DialogTitle>Keyboard Shortcuts</DialogTitle>
          <Input
            placeholder="Search shortcuts..."
            value={search}
            onChange={(e) => setSearch(e.target.value)}
          />
        </DialogHeader>

        {Object.entries(filtered).map(([category, items]) => (
          <div key={category}>
            <h3>{category}</h3>
            {items.map(shortcut => (
              <ShortcutRow key={shortcut.id} shortcut={shortcut} />
            ))}
          </div>
        ))}
      </DialogContent>
    </Dialog>
  );
}
```

